Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Place beef bones on large baking sheet; bake for 15 minutes. Add onion halves to baking sheet; bake 45 minutes more. Place roasted bones and onion in a pressure cooker with carrot, celery, parsley, garlic, salt, peppercorns, thyme, and bay leaves. Pour water up to the 6-quart mark inside pressure cooker; cover with lid and cook according to manufacturer's instructions, about 1 hour. Remove from heat; open pressure cooker carefully.